    "This discrepancy may be attributed to the similar spatial distribution of industry features within the category, resulting in reduced classification accuracy due to interference from these similar features.",
    "While the RCA model's architecture achieves effective classification on diverse datasets, RSSCN7's inherent complexity underscores the need for further optimization or additional contextual modeling to enhance feature discrimination across closely resembling classes.Our analysis suggests that certain dataset characteristics, such as the level of inter-class similarity and the visual complexity of scenes, significantly impact the RCA network's performance.",
    "The differences in results across PatternNet, EuroSAT, and RSSCN7 reveal the RCA network's sensitivity to clear spatial features and class boundaries.",
    "While the Residual Channel-attention network (RCA) demonstrates significant advancements in high-resolution remote sensing image scene classification, it is essential to acknowledge certain limitations that emerged during our study.",
    "One notable consideration is the sensitivity of the RCA network to specific dataset characteristics, such as imbalances or variations in scene complexity."
